🗳️ Decentralized Voting System (Hybrid Web2 + Web3)

📌 Overview

This project is a secure and transparent voting system that combines traditional web technologies with blockchain.

- Web2 (Node.js + MongoDB) → handles user authentication and verification
- Web3 (Ethereum + Smart Contract) → handles voting and result storage

The goal is to ensure:

- ✅ Only verified users can vote
- ✅ Votes cannot be tampered with
- ✅ Results are transparent and auditable

---

🚀 Features

🔐 Authentication & Authorization

- User registration and login using email/password
- JWT-based authentication
- Passwords securely hashed

🪪 User Verification (Off-chain)

- Users submit ID details (Aadhaar/College ID)
- Only hashed ID is stored (privacy-safe)
- Admin approves/rejects users

👛 Wallet Integration

- MetaMask wallet connection
- Wallet address used as blockchain identity

🗳️ Blockchain Voting

- Votes are recorded using a smart contract
- One wallet = one vote enforced
- Voting time window enforced

📊 Results Dashboard

- Real-time results fetched from blockchain
- Transparent and tamper-proof

🧾 Audit System

- Each vote has a transaction hash
- Fully traceable and verifiable

---

🏗️ Tech Stack

Frontend

- React.js
- wagmi / viem (Web3 integration)

Backend

- Node.js
- Express.js
- JWT Authentication

Database

- MongoDB

Blockchain

- Solidity (Smart Contract)
- Hardhat (Local Blockchain)
- MetaMask (Wallet)

---

⚙️ Project Architecture

Frontend (React)
→ Backend (Node.js + MongoDB) → User verification
→ Blockchain (Ethereum Smart Contract) → Voting

---

🔄 How It Works

1. User Authentication

- User registers/logs in
- Backend generates JWT

2. Verification

- User submits ID
- Admin approves → user becomes verified

3. Wallet Connection

- User connects MetaMask
- Wallet address becomes identity on blockchain

4. Voting

- User clicks vote
- Smart contract records vote
- Ensures one vote per wallet

5. Results & Audit

- Results fetched from blockchain
- Transactions visible with hash

---

🧪 Local Setup (Development)

1. Start Hardhat Node

npx hardhat node

---

2. Deploy Contract

npm run deploy:local

---

3. Run Backend

npm run server

---

4. Run Frontend

cd frontend
npm run dev

---

5. Setup MetaMask

- Add network:
  
  - RPC: http://127.0.0.1:8545
  - Chain ID: 31337

- Import Hardhat account (from terminal output)

---

💡 Unique Selling Points (USP)

- 🔥 Hybrid Web2 + Web3 architecture
- 🔐 Verified voting (prevents fake users)
- 🗳️ One wallet = one vote (smart contract enforced)
- 📊 Transparent real-time results
- 🧾 Fully auditable system
- 🔒 Privacy-preserving (hashed identity data)

---

⚠️ Current Limitations

- Voting system works on local blockchain (Hardhat)
- Not deployed to public testnet/mainnet yet
- Admin approval is centralized

---

🔮 Future Improvements

- Deploy to Ethereum testnet (Sepolia)
- Add decentralized identity (DID)
- Improve UI/UX
- Add multi-election support
- Gas optimization

---

🧠 Conclusion

This project demonstrates how combining traditional backend systems with blockchain can create a secure, transparent, and tamper-proof voting system, solving major issues present in conventional voting methods.